The paper discusses a novel approach for training auto-encoders to learn robust and invariant features. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, given the focus on feature learning and classification, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
